{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Reproduction Steps\n`docs/concurrency.md:305` links `([story 23d2-e0f3](../session-logs/2026-06-09-architecture-review.md) Rec 2)` but no `session-logs/` directory exists in the repo (session logs live in the rebar tickets store, not the filesystem).\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: the reference resolves, or points at the story id without a broken file link.\n- Actual: dead relative link to a nonexistent `../session-logs/...md` file.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/concurrency.md:305` no longer contains a dead link — either drop the file link and reference the story id in prose, or point at a real target.\n- [ ] `grep -n 'session-logs/2026-06-09' docs/concurrency.md` returns nothing.\n\n## Notes\nDiscovered while building the f088 docs-index/dead-link CI gate. Out of f088's scope: that gate only validates links resolving INSIDE docs/, and this link escapes docs/ (`../session-logs/`). A whole-repo markdown-link checker would catch it; filed separately so f088 stays scoped.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783825050649187001,"uuid":"6cc7dacd-0172-4f0f-ba4f-55d2ec08e566"}